            <section xml:id="class_q_c_p_line_ending_1a580e4e2360b35ebb8d68f3494aa2335d">
                <title>void QCPLineEnding::setInverted (bool inverted)</title> <emphasis></emphasis>
                
<para>Sets whether the ending decoration shall be inverted. For example, an arrow decoration will point inward when <emphasis>inverted</emphasis> is set to true.</para>

<para>Note that also the <emphasis>width</emphasis> direction is inverted. For symmetrical ending styles like arrows or discs, this doesn&apos;t make a difference. However, asymmetric styles like <link linkend="class_q_c_p_line_ending_1a5ef16e6876b4b74959c7261d8d4c2cd5a126c390f0c359fcd8df1fc5e38d26d5b">esHalfBar</link> are affected by it, which can be used to control to which side the half bar points to. </para>

            </section>
